title: ADDITIONAL FEATURE: Users can Check Positive Attributes about the Food Item
ADDITIONAL FEATURE: Search for Food Items Based off Tags/Categories
FEATURE: Tags/Categories of Food Item Displayed in Food Item Page
FEATURE: Food Item is Given Healthy Rating
FEATURE: Rating of Restaurant is Displayed on Food Item Page
FEATURE: Suggestions of Similar Dishes is Display on Food Item Page
FEATURE: Map View of Restaurant Location is Displayed on Food Item Page
FEATURE: Allow Restaurants to Upload Their Data
Create Detailed View of Food Item Page
Set Up Intial Food Item Database
Create Sign Up Flow
body:
Priority: High

**Acceptance Criteria:**

- User is provided a button to set up an account that they can successfully click
- User is able to provide a valid original username and valid password and make an account that is stored in the database
- User is not able to create an account with a username that is taken
- User's favourite cuisine types data is captured and stored in database
- User's dietary restrictions data is captured and stored in the database
- User's diet goals are captured and stored in the database
- User is able to log in with created account

Tasks:
- [ ] Implement code for sign up button
- [ ] Button takes users to a new web page for signing up for an account (could be multi-step flow)
- [ ] Implement code for a text box to enter in a username
- [ ] Throw exception if username is already stored in the database
- [ ] Implement code for a text box to enter in a password
- [ ] Implement code for a text box to confirm password
- [ ] Throw exception if confirm password doesn't match previously entered password in password text box
- [ ] Capture user's favourite cuisine types by showing them options and having them select
- [ ] Capture user's dietary restrictions by showing them options and having them select
- [ ] Capture user's diet goals by showing them options and having them select
- [ ] Implement code for register button that stores all the data gathered, along with username and password, as an account in the database and takes the user to the home page as being logged in.
